{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"slug":1,"metadata":2,"images":102,"html":185,"xml":233},"ISic004502",{"file":1,"uri":1,"title":3,"status":4,"editions":6,"editionAuthor":17,"type":18,"support":22,"objectType":23,"material":27,"condition":31,"dimensions":33,"layoutDesc":44,"handNote":57,"date":70,"places":75,"geo":84,"provenance":77,"provenanceFound":88,"provenanceGeo":96,"provenanceObserved":97,"provenanceLost":17,"graphics":102,"country":110,"region":111,"settlement":81,"repository":112,"idno":125,"textLang":128,"bibliographyEdition":132,"bibliographyDiscussion":145,"citation":148,"tmNumber":165,"facsimile":166,"letterHeights":167,"publications":170,"zotero":172,"keywords":174,"lettering_types":184},"Section of an inscribed architrave",{"_":5},"draft",[7,9,11,13,15],{"type":8},"TM",{"type":10},"EDR",{"type":12},"EDH",{"type":14},"EDCS",{"type":16},"PHI",null,{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"building","#function.building","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/86.html","Two thin, isolated marble fragments, contiguous and composed in turn of reassembled elements: the first consists of four sections, the second of three. An upper marginal lacuna is visible, especially in the second fragment on the right. The piece appears to belong to an architrave, possibly constructed from separate panels, as the relatively clean-cut edge on the left might suggest. A moulding is partially preserved along the lower edge. The surface is smooth and carefully finished, with traces of lime and minor abrasions; the back is polished.",{"_":24,"ana":25,"ref":26},"architrave","object.arch_element.architrave","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/119.html",{"_":28,"ana":29,"ref":30},"marble","#material.stone.marble","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html",{"ana":32},"#condition.fragments.contiguous",[34,38,41],{"_":35,"unit":36,"dimension":37},"9-16","cm","height",{"_":39,"unit":36,"dimension":40},"88","width",{"_":42,"unit":36,"dimension":43},"0.7-1","depth",{"layout":45},{"p":46,"rs":47,"damage":55},"Part of a line of Latin text with a perfectly straight alignment. Traces of a guideline. Traces of part of a letter remain on the right: a stroke aligned with the break line",[48,52],{"_":49,"ana":50,"ref":51},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"_":53,"ana":54},"rubrication","#execution.rubrication",{"ana":56},"text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":58,"dimensions":59},"Elegant square capital letters, slightly verticalized, uniform and evenly spaced, with serifs and minimal traces of rubrication: E with parallel strokes, circular C, R with a closed loop, P with an open loop, A with a vertical crossbar. Words are separated by interpuncts.",[60,66],{"type":61,"l":62,"from":63,"to":63,"h":64,"unit":65,"atLeast":64,"atMost":64},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","110","mm",{"type":67,"l":68,"from":63,"to":69,"unit":65},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line2",{"_":71,"notBefore":72,"notAfter":73,"evidence":74},"Late first to second century CE",75,200,"lettering",[76,80],{"_":77,"type":78,"ref":79},"Centuripae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153",{"_":81,"type":82,"ref":83},"Centuripe","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525032",[85],[86,87],37.62336,14.74049,{"_":89,"type":90,"subtype":91,"when":92,"geo":93},"Discovered by Guido Libertini during the excavation campaigns conducted starting in 1925, within the complex of spaces near the so-called former Barbagallo Mill, i.g. the area of public buildings near the so-called \"Edificio degli Augustales\" , in a zone overlooking the Vallata Difesa. The contextual information is not very clear. Specifically, the author states that the fragments, and others, were found either «nelle immediate vicinanze dell'edificio rettangolare» or in small rooms «a sud dell'edificio, tra esso e il mulino».","found","discovered","1925",[94,95],37.62257,14.74099,[94,95],{"_":98,"type":99,"subtype":100,"xml:id":101,"geo":17},"Prado 2023-05-09","observed","autopsied","autopsy",[103],{"n":104,"url":105,"height":106,"width":107,"desc":108,"surfaceType":109},"screen","ISic000000_tiled.tif","3680px","5520px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","front","Italy","Sicily",{"_":113,"role":114,"ref":115,"museum":116},"Museo Archeologico Regionale di Centuripe","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/002",{"slug":117,"type":114,"name":113,"uri":115,"description":118,"location":119},"002","An excellent and comprehensive display of archaeological material from Centuripe and the surrounding area",{"settlement":81,"region":120,"country":110,"address":121,"geo":122},"Enna","Via Giulio Cesare, 94010 Centuripe (EN)",{"lat":123,"lon":124},37.622753,14.740806,{"_":126,"type":127},"KA0851","inventory",{"_":129,"mainLang":130,"languages":131},"Latin","la",[129],{"type":133,"bibl":134},"edition",[135],{"author":136,"date":137,"citedRange":138,"ptr":139,"ref":141,"title":81,"citation":143,"uri":144},"Libertini","1926","44 c",{"target":140},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/VJZRAI26",{"_":142,"target":142},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874","\u003Cspan>Guido Libertini, \u003Ci>Centuripe\u003C/i> (Catania, 1926)\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/VJZRAI26",{"type":146,"bibl":147},"discussion",[17],{"editor":149,"principal":152,"contributors":155,"change":162},{"_":150,"ref":151},"Jonathan Prag","#JP",{"_":153,"ref":154},"Francesca Prado","#FP",[156,159],{"_":150,"xml:id":157,"ref":158},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":153,"xml:id":160,"ref":161},"FP","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3326-3475",{"_":163,"when":164,"who":154},"Francesca Prado edited the text, added English and Italian translation and commentary.","2025-09-02","",{"n":104,"url":105,"height":106,"width":107,"desc":108,"surfaceType":109},[168],{"atLeast":169,"atMost":169},110,[171],"Libertini, 1926, Centuripe",[173],"VJZRAI26",[175,176,177,19,24,28,178,179,180,181,179,182,183,130],"isic004502","section of an inscribed architrave",{"_":5},"centuripae","centuripe","italy","sicily","museo archeologico regionale di centuripe","latin",[],{"title":186,"body":187,"divs":188,"editions":215,"images":225,"handnote":231},"ISic004502. Section of an inscribed architrave","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] et · \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Celer\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Celer\">Celer\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · pater · eṭ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ET·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Celer\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Celer\">CELER\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·PATER·E.[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000000_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000000_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000000.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000000-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan> Libertini: ei[us]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3326-3475\">Francesca Prado\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>...and Celer father and...\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3326-3475\">Francesca Prado\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>...e Celer padre e...\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Given the context of discovery, possibly part of a public building erected or restored by one or more members of the local elite (?). In the same area, Libertini also discovered \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003398\" target=\"_blank\">I.Sicily003398\u003C/a> which might possibly refer to a Pompeius Ce[ler]. Libertini himself used the cognomen Celer, attested in this inscription, in order to restore \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003398\" target=\"_blank\">I.Sicily003398\u003C/a>. Libertini proposed the restoration 'Pater eius'; however, the break on the right side of the slab, corresponding to the vertical stroke of a letter, would seem to rule out the presence of a U. Judging from the presence of an 'et' following the cognomen Celer, it is possible that another dedicator was mentioned after him. \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Libertini 1926 44 c \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Elegant square capital letters, slightly verticalized, uniform and evenly spaced, with serifs and minimal traces of rubrication: E with parallel strokes, circular C, R with a closed loop, P with an open loop, A with a vertical crossbar. Words are separated by interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 1  110  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[189,192,195,198,201,203,206,209,212],{"id":190,"html":191},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] et · \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Celer\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Celer\">Celer\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · pater · eṭ [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ET·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Celer\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"cognomen\" data-text=\"Celer\">CELER\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·PATER·E.[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":193,"html":194},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000000_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000000_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000000.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000000-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":196,"html":197},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan> Libertini: ei[us]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":199,"html":200},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3326-3475\">Francesca Prado\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>...and Celer father and...\u003C/p>  ",{"id":199,"html":202},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3326-3475\">Francesca Prado\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>...e Celer padre e...\u003C/p>  ",{"id":204,"html":205},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Given the context of discovery, possibly part of a public building erected or restored by one or more members of the local elite (?). In the same area, Libertini also discovered \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003398\" target=\"_blank\">I.Sicily003398\u003C/a> which might possibly refer to a Pompeius Ce[ler]. Libertini himself used the cognomen Celer, attested in this inscription, in order to restore \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003398\" target=\"_blank\">I.Sicily003398\u003C/a>. Libertini proposed the restoration 'Pater eius'; however, the break on the right side of the slab, corresponding to the vertical stroke of a letter, would seem to rule out the presence of a U. Judging from the presence of an 'et' following the cognomen Celer, it is possible that another dedicator was mentioned after him. \u003C/p>  ",{"id":207,"html":208},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Libertini 1926 44 c \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":210,"html":211},"handnote"," \u003Cp>Elegant square capital letters, slightly verticalized, uniform and evenly spaced, with serifs and minimal traces of rubrication: E with parallel strokes, circular C, R with a closed loop, P with an open loop, A with a vertical crossbar. Words are separated by interpuncts.\u003C/p> Line 1  110  Interlineation line 1 to 2    ",{"id":213,"html":214},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[216,218,221,222],{"html":217},"Text encoding: Francesca Prado; edition source: autopsy Prado 2023-05-09",{"id":219,"lang":130,"html":220},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"a